            <title>Detailed Description</title>

<para>A field which if blank takes the value of another model field mangled to be same format as a URLSegment. Does not change if the source field changes, only if it is empty. </para>
                <para>Definition at line 13 of file ModelTag.php</para>
                <para>The Documentation for this struct was generated from the following file: </para>
                <para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>ModelTag.php</para></listitem></itemizedlist></para>
        </simplesect>
            <section xml:id="d3/d5b/class_modular_1_1_fields_1_1_model_tag_1a340b4667ab68f54a142c6ecbf8629ead">
                <title>__construct ($sourceFieldName= &apos;Title&apos;, $parentIDFieldName= &apos;&apos;, $fallbackFieldName= &apos;&apos;)</title> <emphasis></emphasis>
                
<para><link linkend="d3/d5b/class_modular_1_1_fields_1_1_model_tag">ModelTag</link> constructor can be used in config to set alternate field names as: extensions:<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para><link linkend="df/df5/namespace_modular">Modular</link>(&apos;<link linkend="d2/dde/class_modular_1_1_fields_1_1_title">Title</link>&apos;, &apos;ParentID&apos;)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>

<para>
                <formalpara>
                    <title/>
                    <table frame="all">
                        <title>Parameters</title>
                        <tgroup cols="2" align="left" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry>$sourceFieldName</entry>
                                <entry>
<para>e.g. &apos;<link linkend="d2/dde/class_modular_1_1_fields_1_1_title">Title</link>&apos; </para>
</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>$parentIDFieldName</entry>
                                <entry>
<para>e.g. &apos;ParentID&apos;, if passed then make the tag distinct within children of the ParentID. </para>
</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>$fallbackFieldName</entry>
                                <entry>
<para>e.g. &apos;URLSegment&apos;, allow another field to be used on parents if they do not have the <link linkend="d3/d5b/class_modular_1_1_fields_1_1_model_tag">ModelTag</link> extension </para>
</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </formalpara>
                </para>

            </section>
